<Link id="l00111" /><CodeLine lineNumber="111"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///   digits            :: &lt;non-negative integer&gt; 0-99</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00114" /><CodeLine lineNumber="114"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///   |  style  |     Meaning          |      Example     | Digits Meaning     |</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00119" /><CodeLine lineNumber="119"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///   |   X-    | Hex no prefix, upper |   42   |    2A   | Minimum # digits   |</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00121" /><CodeLine lineNumber="121"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///   | X+ / X  | Hex + prefix, upper  |   42   |   42  | Minimum # digits   |</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00122" /><CodeLine lineNumber="122"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///   | N / n   | Digit grouped number | 123456 | 123,456 | Ignored            |</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00278" /><CodeLine lineNumber="278"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// Implementation of format&#95;provider&lt;T&gt; for floating point types.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00279" /><CodeLine lineNumber="279"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00280" /><CodeLine lineNumber="280"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// The options string of a floating point type has the format:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00281" /><CodeLine lineNumber="281"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00282" /><CodeLine lineNumber="282"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///   float&#95;options   :: &#91;style&#93;&#91;precision&#93;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00283" /><CodeLine lineNumber="283"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///   style           :: &lt;see table below&gt;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00284" /><CodeLine lineNumber="284"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///   precision       :: &lt;non-negative integer&gt; 0-99</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00285" /><CodeLine lineNumber="285"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00286" /><CodeLine lineNumber="286"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///   =====================================================</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00287" /><CodeLine lineNumber="287"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///   |  style  |     Meaning          |      Example     |</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00288" /><CodeLine lineNumber="288"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///   -----------------------------------------------------</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00289" /><CodeLine lineNumber="289"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///   |         |                      |  Input |  Output |</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00290" /><CodeLine lineNumber="290"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///   =====================================================</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00291" /><CodeLine lineNumber="291"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///   | P / p   | Percentage           |  0.05  |  5.00%  |</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00292" /><CodeLine lineNumber="292"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///   | F / f   | Fixed point          |   1  |  1   |</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00293" /><CodeLine lineNumber="293"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///   |   E     | Exponential with E   | 100000 | 100000 |</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00294" /><CodeLine lineNumber="294"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///   |   e     | Exponential with e   | 100000 | 100000 |</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00295" /><CodeLine lineNumber="295"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///   | (empty) | Same as F / f        |        |         |</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00296" /><CodeLine lineNumber="296"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///   =====================================================</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00297" /><CodeLine lineNumber="297"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00298" /><CodeLine lineNumber="298"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// The default precision is 6 for exponential (E / e) and 2 for everything</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00299" /><CodeLine lineNumber="299"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// else.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00300" /><CodeLine lineNumber="300"></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00339" /><CodeLine lineNumber="339"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// Implementation of format&#95;provider&lt;T&gt; for ranges.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00340" /><CodeLine lineNumber="340"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00341" /><CodeLine lineNumber="341"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// This will print an arbitrary range as a delimited sequence of items.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00342" /><CodeLine lineNumber="342"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00343" /><CodeLine lineNumber="343"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// The options string of a range type has the grammar:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00344" /><CodeLine lineNumber="344"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00345" /><CodeLine lineNumber="345"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///   range&#95;style       ::= &#91;separator&#93; &#91;element&#95;style&#93;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00346" /><CodeLine lineNumber="346"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///   separator         ::= &quot;$&quot; delimeted&#95;expr</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00347" /><CodeLine lineNumber="347"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///   element&#95;style     ::= &quot;@&quot; delimeted&#95;expr</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00348" /><CodeLine lineNumber="348"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///   delimeted&#95;expr    ::= &quot;&#91;&quot; expr &quot;&#93;&quot; | &quot;(&quot; expr &quot;)&quot; | &quot;&lt;&quot; expr &quot;&gt;&quot;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00349" /><CodeLine lineNumber="349"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///   expr              ::= &lt;any string not containing delimeter&gt;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00350" /><CodeLine lineNumber="350"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00351" /><CodeLine lineNumber="351"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// where the separator expression is the string to insert between consecutive</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00352" /><CodeLine lineNumber="352"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// items in the range and the argument expression is the Style specification to</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00353" /><CodeLine lineNumber="353"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// be used when formatting the underlying type.  The default separator if</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00354" /><CodeLine lineNumber="354"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// unspecified is &#39; &#39; (space).  The syntax of the argument expression follows</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00355" /><CodeLine lineNumber="355"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// whatever grammar is dictated by the format provider or format adapter used</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00356" /><CodeLine lineNumber="356"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// to format the value type.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00357" /><CodeLine lineNumber="357"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00358" /><CodeLine lineNumber="358"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// Note that attempting to format an &#96;iterator&#95;range&lt;T&gt;&#96; where no format</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00359" /><CodeLine lineNumber="359"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// provider can be found for T will result in a compile error.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00360" /><CodeLine lineNumber="360"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00361" /><CodeLine lineNumber="361"></CodeLine>
